* Gaussian Blur- smooths the image by averaging pixel values with its neighbours
* WHY IT IS CALLED GAUSSIAN BLUR?? --- >> because average has Gaussian Falloff effects.
* pixels that are closer to the target pixel have a higher impact with the average than pixels that are far away and this is how smoothing workss!!
* WHY SMOOTHING???? ---->>> to smooth out the noise in an image as a precursor to other processing.
